data.content:
**In .NET 11, all synchronous I/O on the EF Core Cosmos DB provider is permanently removed.** The `.NET 10 opt-in` (`EnableSyncIO` / sync-over-async) no longer exists — calling any sync API **always throws** at runtime, with no workaround.

Your four broken calls and their fixes:

```csharp
// ❌ All of these throw in EF Core 11
_context.Products.ToList();
_context.Products.First(p => p.Id == id);
_context.Products.Count();
_context.SaveChanges();

// ✅ Convert to async
public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    => await _context.Products.ToListAsync();

public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    => await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);

public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    => await _context.Products.CountAsync();

public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
{
    _context.Products.Add(product);
    await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
}
```

This will cascade — all callers of these methods must also become `async`/`await` up the call chain (controllers, services, etc.). There is **no opt-in to restore sync behavior** in EF Core 11.
